<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-28T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-28T07:00:00-05:00" n="827" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d827">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/12–2845: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iraq</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Moose</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Baghdad</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-28T15:00:00+03:00">December
                                    28, 1945—3 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 4:01 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>515. Reference Legation’s telegram No. 509, December 21, 5 p.m. No local
                            official has mentioned to Legation Congressional resolutions <pb facs="0856" n="844" xml:id="pg_844"/> on Palestine nor has usual
                            note of protest been received from Foreign Ministry. Possibly Iraqi
                            officials now consider United States as irrevocably in Zionist camp.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Moose</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>